FBIS4-54468 "dreeu084_i_94005" FBIS-EEU-94-084 Daily Report 1 May 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Two U.S. Reporters Killed by Mine Two U.S. Reporters Killed by Mine LD0105204594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 1 May 94 LD0105204594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] Two U.S. journalists were killed and one was injured in Bosnia-Herzegovina today. For as yet unknown reasons their car skidded off the Sarajevo-Mostar road and hit a mine. Brian Bringhton of the (Magnolia) news agency and Francis Willian Tomasich of the Spin agency. William Wallman of the Spin agency suffered slight injuries, a spokesman for the Spanish battalion has told HABENA in Medjugorje. An UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] patrol has taken the wounded reporter to Dracevo's hospital.
